The paper discusses the implementation and performance of Neural Turing Machines (NTMs), which are a type of Memory Augmented Neural Network. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which suggest the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as likely options. Finally, the paper also mentions sequence learning tasks, which could potentially fall under the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
